a_4.informal problem:
We define a function $p(x, y)$ as follows:
- If $x$ and $y$ are both nonnegative, then $p(x, y) = x + y$;
- If $x$ and $y$ are both negative, then $p(x, y) = x - 2y$;
- Otherwise, $p(x, y) = 3x + y$.

Given this, find the value of $p(p(1, -1), p(-5, -2))$. The final answer is $5$.

a_6.informal problem:
Define a function $p(x, y)$ as follows:

$$
p(x, y) = \begin{cases}
x + y, & \text{if } x \ge 0 \text{ and } y \ge 0 \\
x - 2y, & \text{if } x < 0 \text{ and } y < 0 \\
3x + y, & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
$$

Find the value of $p(p(1, -1), p(-5, -2))$. The final answer is $5$.
